    <h1 style="margin-bottom:.75rem;">About</h1>
    <p>LAonFilm is a love letter to Los Angeles, captured on instant film with a vintage Hasselblad 500cm camera.</p>

    <p>What started as a small project for Airbnb guests—sharing Polaroids on the fridge with QR codes—has grown into a way to highlight the historical, kitschy, fun, and beautiful spots that make this city unique.</p>

    <p>The process is entirely analog: I use a <strong>Hasselblad 500cm</strong>, a classic medium-format film camera from the 1970s, fitted with the <a href="https://www.hassypb.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HassyPB</a> back. This ingenious back allows the camera to shoot <strong>Fujifilm Instax Square</strong> instant film, turning each photo into a one-of-a-kind Polaroid straight out of a professional studio camera. It combines the craft of medium-format photography with the immediacy and charm of instant film.</p>

    <p>The goal is simple: to slow down, shoot intentionally, and celebrate the Los Angeles I love.</p>

